{
  "stem": "3524.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had soluble tablets that we had to mix up just prior to the administration of the penicillin and-- so I would show them how we'd use normal saline or sterile water and put the tablet in the vial and mix up the appropriate strength for the injections.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You're referring to the prisoners who were also doctors at this point?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the prisoners were taking care of-- yes, they were also doctors, but they were taking care of the, the hospitalized prisoners.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In my estimation, all of them should have been in a hospital, but the ones that were surgically required to be in a hospital where there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Some of the more severe cases were hospitalized.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Why they-- how they selected who was to go to a hospital and who was not, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They left that in charge of the doctors in that, in that particular-- we were usually, we were used primarily as advisors and what they might be able to accomplish with what they had.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I never was aware of any big reaction.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I found out later that some of them who did speak Yiddish did get together with some of the prisoners, and they begin to exchange some of the stories.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "These didn't come out until well after we'd left the camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they had talked about what transpired prior to their commitment to the concentration camp and some of the hardships that they had to endure during the camp stay.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Pretty much of that had been cleared out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We did see the infamous lampshades made of human skin that were collected by the camp commander and his wife.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "His wife was particularly fond of collecting tattoos.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there were tattoos that were mounted on plaques.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
